Digitized by the folks at [Virtual AGC][3] and [MIT Museum][4]. The goal is to be a repo for the original Apollo 11 source code. As such, PRs are welcome for any issues identified between the transcriptions in this repository and the original source scans for [Luminary 099][5] and [Comanche 055][6], as well as any files I may have missed. ## Contributing Please read [CONTRIBUTING.md][7] before opening a pull request. ## Compiling If you are interested in compiling the original source code, check out [Virtual AGC][8]. ## Attribution   |   :------------- | :----- Copyright | Public domain Comanche055 | Part of the source code for Colossus 2A, the Command Module's (CM) Apollo Guidance Computer (AGC) for Apollo 11
